@NODE WhatIs "What is Chat-O-Meter - ® KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                          - -----------------------.
                         |  What Is Chat-O-Meter?  |
                         `----------------------- -

   Chat-O-Meter  is  a  small tool that keeps track of all your chats, in
   particulair  the  length  of  all  your  chats  with users.  With this
   information it is able to create a nice looking @{"bulletin" link BullExample} that displays
   a Top Ten of all times.

   Besides  that,  it  also saves the times of the chats per user. At the
   end  of  every  chat,  the  user  gets  to  see  his  or  her personal
   information such as the overall score and total number of chats he/she
   was engaged in.

   This  only  takes up a small amount of time and hardly any disk space.
   The  creation of the bulletin only takes up about 1 sec (on a standard
   machine,  it's  even  quicker  on 020+ systems) and the file size of a
   file that holds 400 users is about 3.5Kb.

   Chat-O-Meter  also  is giftware, do with it what you want, but you may
   not  sell  it.  Distribution on AmiNet is allowed, but distribution on
   PD  series  is  forbidden  (I  don't  like  people  making money of my
   products).

   Anyway,  this  version has been totally rewritten from scratch and now
   has a cool logo made by Stezothetic, so enjoy it!

                                                        @{"-KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC" link Contact}
@ENDNODE

@NODE WhatsNew "What's New in version 2.0 - ® KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                           - --------------------.
                          |  New in version 2.0  |
                          `-------------------- -

   The  previous  version ( 1.2 ) was released over one year ago (October
   1993)  and  to tell you the truth, the coding was lousy and it was not
   that  sysop  friendly.   But  do  not  despair,  this version has been
   totally rewritten (from scratch!) and is much smarter and has got some
   nice new options.  Better forget all about the previous version :-)

   It  has  to  be  said  that I would have never created this version if
   Quartz  hadn't  asked  for  it  AND if Stezothetic hadn't made such an
   awesome logo.  It seems people use my tools after all :-)

   First  of  all,  the best improvement is that it is now able to detect
   wether you started or ended a chat.  So if you were a previous user of
   Chat-O-Meter,  the  times  of  deleting  the  old data file before you
   started another chat are over :) Lost carriers are no problem anymore.

   Another  *BIG* improvement is the @{"new layout" link BullExample}, done by Stezo (Stz).  It
   now  has  got a really great logo and nice colours.  You'll love it, I
   do!  Many thanks to Stezothetic for creating the logo!

   What  also  new is, is the fact that a record is kept of all chats per
   user.   One  file is kept that contains all information about ALL your
   chats ever (since you started to use CoM ofcoz) per user.  I will also
   create  a  door/tool that creates a nice bulletin out of that one.  If
   you  think  this  is  nonsense, you are able to turn it off so no data
   file will be created.

   The  previous  version also did not set the ENV:  variable of AMi-X to
   the right value, so users that performed a 'who' saw that the user you
   were  chatting  with was 'using a door'.  This has been fixed.  But if
   you  liked  that 'feature' of Chat-O-Meter, it is still able to hide a
   chat. Privacy above all (nope, there is no PGP function :) ).

   That's it.  I hope you'll like it, it's one of those nice little doors
   that  makes  just  the  difference  between your board and your follow
   sysops' boards.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Features "Features of Chat-O-Meter - ® KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                      - ------------------------------.
                     |  Features of Chat-O-Meter 2.0  |
                     `------------------------------ -

   Ł Creates a bulletin wherever you want (configurable)

   Ł Very nice/cool layout thanks to Stezothetic (Stz)

   Ł Ability to hide a chat from other users

   Ł Fast creation of data files and bulletin
   
   Ł Small data files (308 bytes and 2 bytes/user)
   
   Ł Keeps track of sysop chats, but also user chats. That is,
     a record is kept per user with his/her personal total chat
     time and total number of chats.
     
   Ł At the end of a chat, a small bulletin is shown stating the
     latest statistics. See @{"example" link ExitChatExample}.
     This is configurable (Quiet mode is available).
     
   Ł Configurable 'Show Bulletin [ Y/n ]' when user has entered
     the Chat-O-Meter Top Ten.
     
   Ł Configurable stripping of plural words ( 1 mIN instead of 1 mINS)

   Ł Easy to use
@ENDNODE

