@NODE Install "Installation of Chat-O-Meter - ® KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                      - -----------------------------.
                     |  How to install Chat-O-Meter  |
                     `----------------------------- -

   First  of  all, you can put the executable (Chat-O-Meter) anywhere you
   like.   The  data  files  will  be  created in that same directory.  I
   suggest  you  put it in DOORS:Chat-O-Meter/ but hey, it's up to you (I
   just  hate  it  when people hard code a path in their program, haven't
   they heard of the PROGDIR:  assign?).

   Secondly,  Chat-O-Meter  needs  to be started with an MCI command from
   the  STARTCHAT.TXT  and  ENDCHAT.TXT  files  that can be found in your
   BBS:NODEx/   directory.    Two   icons   have   been  supplied  called
   `Chat_Start.info'  and  `Chat_End.info'.   I recommend you put them in
   your  BBS:Commands/SYSCmd/  directory,  as  is  standard with commands
   started with an MCI command.

   For  those sysops who don't know how to implement Chat-O-Meter in your
   STARTCHAT.TXT  and  ENDCHAT.TXT,  make  sure the text files contain at
   least the following lines:

                 STARTCHAT.TXT           ENDCHAT.TXT
                 -------------           -----------
                 ~                       ~
                 ~CC_CHAT_START          ~CC_CHAT_END

   It  doesn't  matter wether you've got a logo in those files.  Just put
   the text in there somewhere.

   Once you have copied the icons to your BBS:Commands/SYSCmd/ directory,
   check out the following tooltypes:

   Chat_Start.info
   ---------------
   STACK=50000          ; Keep it this high, everything is done on stack
   There are no more tooltypes for this icon.
   
   Chat_End.info
   -------------
   CHAT_END             : This  is how Chat-O-Meter recognizes the end of
                          a chat. Make sure it is in this icon!

   BULLETIN=            : This  is where you can specify how the bulletin
                          should be called and where it should be created
                          (i.e. BULLETIN=BBS:Bulletins/Chat-O-Meter.TXT)

   DONT_ASK             : Normally,  whenever  a user gets in the Top Ten
                          of Chat-O-Meter,  he/she  will  be asked wether
                          the  Chat-O-Meter  bulletin  should be shown to
                          them. However, if you specify this tooltype, no
                          questions  will  be  asked  and nothing will be
                          shown.

   DONT_TRUNC           : By  default  all plural 's'-es will be removed.
                          So  for  example:  1 hOURS  becomes 1 hOUR  and
                          1 sECS  becomes  1 sEC.  However,  if you think
                          that  ruins  the  bulletin (cosmetically),  you
                          can  override  it  by specifying this tooltype.
                          All plural 's'-es will be left alone.

   QUIET                : Whenever  a chat is ended,  a small bulletin is
                          shown  with  the  latest  statistics about that
                          chat.  However,  if  you do not want this to be
                          shown,  specify this tooltype and the user will
                          even know you are using Chat-O-Meter.  No,  not
                          even a copyright message ;-)

   NO_USERFILE          : This  version  of  Chat-O-Meter  creates a file
                          that  contains  all  chat information about the
                          users,   one  by  one.  So  Chat-O-Meter  knows
                          from  every  user,  how long he/she has chatted
                          and  how many times you have chatted with them.
                          It  doesn't  take  up  much space,  with around
                          400  users  you will get a file of about 3.5KB.
                          If  you  feel  this  is  useless or you have no
                          need  for  this,  insert this tooltype and that
                          file   will  not  be  created  plus  the  small
                          bulletin at the end of a chat will be smaller.

   That are all tooltypes for this moment.  When you are done setting the
   tooltypes  you  are ready with the installation of Chat-O-Meter.  Have
   fun and chat your head off!  :-)
@ENDNODE

@NODE BullExample "Bulletin Example Output - Design by Stezothetic!"

   ASCII  never looks good in AmigaGuide or MultiView, but you'll get the
   idea anyway I hope.
   
   If  you  might wonder why there are multiple entries for one user, the
   Chat-O-Meter  Top  Ten  is  sorted  by  the length of the chat, and it
   doesn't matter wether a user is present several times in it.
   
   This  is  not because I am to lazy to built in that check, but suppose
   you have a chat of 5 hours with somebody.  The next time you chat with
   him,  you  have a chat of 7 hours.  Does this mean I should just erase
   that  5  hour  chat and mention the 7 hour chat?  I think not, that is
   not  fair.   A  5  hour chat is just as cool as a 7 hour chat and they
   both deserve to be mentioned.

