@NODE Conversion "How to convert your old bulletin - ® 1995 KiLLraVeN/MYSTiC"
                           - ---------------------.
                          |  Bulletin Conversion  |
                          `--------------------- -

   For  sysops  that  used  Chat-O-Meter  1.x, there is a special program
   called  "CoM-Convert"  that allows you to convert your old bulletin to
   the  new  data  file  that  Chat-O-Meter  2.0  uses.  If you are not a
   previous user of Chat-O-Meter, you can skip this part.

   To  convert  it,  simply  start  the  program  "CoM-Convert"  from the
   directory  where  you  have Chat-O-Meter 2.0 installed.  The data file
   will be created in the directory where you started "CoM-Convert".

   Once  you  have  started the program, a file requester will pop up and
   you  must select the old bulletin.  Press `OK' and you will get to see
   the names (plus additional info) from that bulletin.

   After that, the program will exit (`Ready.') and you can find the data
   file  called  `Chat-O-Meter.Data'  in that same directory.  Move it if
   you  have  to.  The new bulletin will not be created yet!  To do this,
   you  have  to  start Chat-O-Meter 2.0 from /X (start and end a chat is
   sufficient).

   That's it, easy a as a fiddle.

   NOTE : To use this tool, you must have req-tools installed.

   NOTE╣: There  is *NO* check whether the file you feed to "CoM-Convert"
          really  is an old bulletin from 1.x.  You can even cheat if you
          want to ;-)

   NOTE▓: To  all beta-testers, this conversion util takes in account any
          old  `Chat-O-Meter.Data' file.  That is, it doesn't recalculate
          a new Top-Ten (it simply converts the old one), but it does ADD
          the  old  `Total Chat Time'  to the new time and that also goes
          for the total number of chats.
@ENDNODE
